<paragraph id="8B9636A2FFE78938FF52FEF8706E9809" blockId="77.[151,1437,151,536]" box="[199,890,332,357]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis id="B95DEAB0FFE78938FF52FEF872BA9809" bold="true" box="[199,430,332,357]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Bathymetric range.</emphasis>
Littoral zone to 
<quantity id="4CD19B47FFE78938FDFCFEF871B69808" box="[617,674,332,356]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" unit="m" value="90.0">90 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB84B53FFE78938FD25FEF870799809" author="Mortensen, T." box="[688,877,332,357]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" refId="ref35636" refString="Mortensen, T. (1951) A Monograph of the Echinoidea V. 2. Spatangoida. 2. Amphisternata. II. Spatangidae, Loveniidae, Pericosmidae, Schizasteridae, Brissidae. C. A. Reitzel, Copenhagen, 593 pp." type="book" year="1951">Mortensen 1951</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9636A2FFE78938FF52FEDB703F98BC" blockId="77.[151,1437,151,536]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis id="B95DEAB0FFE78938FF52FEDB716598E4" bold="true" box="[199,625,367,392]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
Observed occurrence in 
<collectingCountry id="F33E7632FFE78938FE7AFEDB717898E4" box="[495,620,367,392]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
Specimens were collected from a sandy bottom with sea grass beds in Silavathurai and Baththalangunduwa, north-western coast of Sri Lanka, at depth range of 
<quantity id="4CD19B47FFE78938FB18FE2077E598C0" box="[1165,1265,404,428]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" unit="m" value="15.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="10.0">10–20 m</quantity>
(
<figureCitation id="13122A27FFE78938FA94FE20764198C1" box="[1281,1365,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 67" captionStartId="76.[151,250,1877,1899]" captionTargetBox="[182,1426,219,1841]" captionTargetId="figure@76.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="FIGURE 67. Distribution map of Metalia sternalis recorded in this study." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2617589/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
). This species was first recorded from Sri Lanka by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB84B53FFE78938FD06FE03703398BC" author="Clark, H. L." box="[659,807,439,464]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="83 - 102" refId="ref34305" refString="Clark, H. L. (1915) The echinoderms of Ceylon other than holothurians. Spolia Zeylanica, 10, 83 - 102." type="journal article" year="1915">Clark (1915)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3336529FFE78938FF52FE68712C9B74" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9636A2FFE78938FF52FE68712C9B74" blockId="77.[151,1437,151,536]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis id="B95DEAB0FFE78938FF52FE68722F9899" bold="true" box="[199,315,476,501]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C294D21FFE78938FED7FE6972DC9899" baseAuthorityName="Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1816" box="[322,456,476,501]" class="Echinoidea" family="Brissidae" genus="Metalia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spatangoida" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="sternalis">
<emphasis id="B95DEAB0FFE78938FED7FE6972DC9899" box="[322,456,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">M. sternalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D21FFE78938FD62FE68705A9899" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1855" box="[759,846,476,501]" class="Echinoidea" family="Brissidae" genus="Metalia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spatangoida" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95DEAB0FFE78938FD62FE68705A9899" box="[759,846,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Metalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. by having a coalescence between the aboralmost regions of the posterior paired petals.
</paragraph>
